{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Give businesses the right to opt out of Business Improvement Districts (BIDs)",
        "additional_details": "I am asking parliament to give businesses the right to opt out of BIDs so they are not required to pay a levy. Many small businesses have high overheads and during this time the Government needs to step in to stop local councils forcing companies to pay money to these BIDs. I am asking that government change the rules for businesses to opt in or opt out of BIDS across England.",
        "background": "During COVID-19 many small shop and business owners are already struggling.\r\n\r\nMany BIDs are set up and councils with companies required to pay a levy. If a company doesn\u2019t pay it can be taken to court! We believe this is unfair is damaging the high street!",
